optimus_cutedsl — licensing
===========================

This directory is a vendored CuTe-DSL kernel package with mixed provenance. See
NOTICE for the per-file attribution map. Three regimes apply:

1. BSD-3-Clause — code derived from NVIDIA CUTLASS and the CuTe-DSL port of
   Dao-AILab/flash-attention. Covered files include (non-exhaustive; see NOTICE):
     symmetric_dense_gemm_sm90.py, gemm_ar/gemm_ar_kernel.py,
     flash_attn/mma_sm100_desc.py, and the flash_attn/flash_{fwd,bwd}*.py family.

2. BSD-3-Clause — the flash-attention CuTe-DSL reimplementation authored by
   Jay Shah, Ganesh Bikshandi, Ying Zhang, Vijay Thakkar, Pradeep Ramani, Tri Dao
   (and contributors Wentao Guo, Ted Zadouri, Markus Hoehnerbach). Upstream:
   https://github.com/Dao-AILab/flash-attention (BSD-3-Clause).

3. MIT — the project-original files (the tail-tree speculative-decode kernel and
   its reference: flash_attn/flash_fwd_sm90_paged_tree.py,
   flash_attn/tail_tree_attn/*, _cutlass_monkeypatch.py, and other unmarked files)
   are released under the MIT license of the parent repository (see ../LICENSE).

The full text of the BSD-3-Clause License governing regimes (1) and (2) follows.

